definition.value: A member of the class of 3-(3,4-substituted-phenyl)-1,1-dimethylureas that is urea in which both of the hydrogens attached to one nitrogen are substituted by methyl groups, and one of the hydrogens attached to the other nitrogen is substituted by a 3,4-dichlorophenyl group.
A member of the class of cyclobutadipyrimidines that is 1,4a,4b,8,8a,8b-hexahydrocyclobuta[1,2-d:4,3-d']dipyrimidine-2,7-dione carrying two additional amino substituents at positions 4 and 5.
